article.headline: New Orleans proves big-time easy
article.story:
NEW ORLEANS (AP) -- Ashley Earley scored a career-high 26 points,
including the 1,000th of her career, to lead Vanderbilt (No. 13 ESPN/USA Today; No. 15  AP) to a
91-37 victory over winless New Orleans on Thursday night.

Cherish Springfield added 12 points, Dee Davis scored 11 and
Caroline Williams had 10 for Vanderbilt (10-1), which forced 21
turnovers and limited New Orleans to 24 percent shooting.

Ashlee Norwood led the 0-11 Lady Privateers with 10 points.

Playing for the first time in nine days, Vanderbilt displayed a
potent scoring attack and stingy defense in dealing the Lady
Privateers their most lopsided loss of the season.

Earley shot 11-for-17 in becoming the 16th player in school
history to score 1,000 points, and Vanderbilt made 58 percent of
its shots in the win.

Vanderbilt won its third game of the season by at least 50
points. The Commodores' smallest margin of victory this season was
a 29-point win over Siena on Nov. 27.

Vanderbilt outrebounded the Privateers 40-32 and finished with
25 assists and nine turnovers.

In the final 20 minutes, the Commodores made 71 percent of their
shots.
